{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0794b681-a8b7-4d32-b959-70a4ba78383a","content":"In .NET MAUI, you use the **lifecycle events API** in `CreateMauiApp()` to hook into platform-specific events:\n\n```csharp\npublic static MauiApp CreateMauiApp()\n{\n    var builder = MauiApp.CreateBuilder();\n    builder.UseMauiApp<App>();\n\n    builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n    {\n#if ANDROID\n        events.AddAndroid(android => android\n            .OnPause(activity => { /* runs on Android pause */ })\n            .OnStop(activity  => { /* runs on Android stop  */ }));\n#elif IOS\n        events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n            .DidEnterBackground(app => { /* runs on iOS background */ }));\n#endif\n    });\n\n    return builder.Build();\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- Call `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` on `MauiAppBuilder`.\n- Use `#if ANDROID` / `#elif IOS` preprocessor directives to target each platform.\n- `AddAndroid` exposes `OnPause`, `OnStop`, `OnResume`, etc.\n- `AddiOS` exposes `DidEnterBackground`, `WillEnterForeground`, etc.\n- Add `using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;` at the top.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6eeb4496-99db-4d8f-be8e-95b86e8ef58c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI. This is a general knowledge question about .NET MAUI development. I can answer this directly without needing to search any codebase.","outputTokens":390,"requestId":"9BC3:335471:5C69664:67A8DF1:69EC0EC8"},"id":"3427667d-b6f2-43a7-bf16-561f7224e98a","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:46:07.781Z","parentId":"b39d053d-9401-4375-a8c7-0bf3d19dae72"}
